In large skillet over medium heat, saute rice-vermicelli mix with margarine and onion until vermicelli is golden brown, stirring frequently. Slowly stir in water, seasonings and undrained diced tomatoes. Stir in chicken, bell pepper and garlic; bring to a boil. Cover; reduce heat to low. Simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until rice is tender. Sprinkle evenly with cheese.